            <title>[THRIFT-1171] Perl write/readDouble assumes little-endian platform</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1171</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The code for handling doubles uses pack &apos;d&apos; (pack to native byte order) and then reverses the bytes. This works on little-endian systems but will produce backwards data on big-endian systems.  Patch is attached.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Any big-endian system such as PPC Mac, Sparc, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
